

The number of licensed vehicles in Macao, a region with a population of nearly 470,000, reached 151, 000 in September, a year-on-year rise of 20 percent.

Statistics issued by the government-run Statistics and Census Service (SCS) Wednesday showed 51 percent of the registered vehicles are motorcycles and 45 percent light vehicles.

The SCS figures showed that there were 9,966 cases of traffic accidents reported in the first three quarters of 2005, a year-on-year increase of 7 percent.

The accidents led to 3,216 casualties, according to the figures.

